'''CSI效应'''（{{lang-en|CSI effect}}）也称'''CSI症候群'''（{{lang-en|CSI syndrome}}）<ref name="Ramsland">{{cite web |title=The CSI Syndrome |author=Ramsland, Katherine |url=http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/criminal_mind/psychology/csi_effect/1_index.html |publisher=Turner Broadcasting System |accessdate=2013-08-09 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130612072950/http://www.trutv.com/library/crime/criminal_mind/psychology/csi_effect/1_index.html |archivedate=2013-06-12 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>{{rp|ch.2}}或'''CSI感染'''（{{lang-en|CSI infection}}）<ref name="Lawson">{{cite journal |title=Before the Verdict and Beyond the Verdict: The CSI Infection Within Modern Criminal Jury Trials |author=Lawson, Tamara F |url=http://www.luc.edu/law/activities/publications/lljdocs/vol41_no1/pdfs/lawson_verdict.pdf |journal=Loyola University Chicago Law Journal |volume=41 |pages=132, 142 |format=PDF |date=2009-11-03 |accessdate=2013-05-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110616170237/http://www.luc.edu/law/activities/publications/lljdocs/vol41_no1/pdfs/lawson_verdict.pdf |archivedate=2011-06-16 }}</ref>，是指因《[[犯罪现场调查|犯罪现场调查]]》之类犯罪题材电视节目中有关[[司法科学|司法科学]]的多种过分夸大描绘而对公众认知产生的影响。这个词語多指一种相信[[陪审团|陪审团]]会在[[刑事诉讼法|刑事案审讯]]过程中要求更多法医证据，从而提高[[检察官|检察官]]有效[[舉證責任_(法律)|举证标准]]的看法。虽然美国法律界专业人士普遍有这样的看法，但一些研究表明单凭犯罪题材的节目并不大可能造成这样的效果，经常观看《犯罪现场调查》的观众也不会过于看重[[间接证据|间接证据]]（circumstantial evidence）<ref name="Shelton2009">{{cite journal | url = http://works.bepress.com/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1012&context=donald_shelton | page = 22 | title = Examining the "CSI-effect" in the cases of circumstantial evidence and eyewitness testimony: Multivariate and path analyses | author = Kim, Young S; Barak, Gregg; Shelton, Donald E | journal = Journal of Criminal Justice | volume = 37 | issue = 5 | year = 2009 | accessdate = 2013-05-28 | doi = 10.1016/j.jcrimjus.2009.07.005 | archive-date = 2013-06-27 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130627102919/http://works.bepress.com/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1012&context=donald_shelton | dead-url = yes }}</ref>。不過随着技术进步，而且科技在整个社会中变得越来越普遍，人们也可能会对法医取证技术有更高的期望<ref name="Washtenaw2">{{cite journal |title=An Indirect-Effects Model of Mediated Adjudication: The CSI Myth, the Tech Effect, and Metropolitan Jurors' Expectations for Scientific Evidence |author=Shelton, Donald E; Kim, Young S; Barak, Gregg |date=2009 Fall |journal=Vanderbilt Journal of Entertainment and Technology Law |volume=12 |issue=1 |page=9 |url=http://washtenawtrialcourt.org/general/judge_profiles/DESresume/DESPubs/JurorsCSIMyth.pdf |accessdate=2013-08-09 |format=PDF |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130617085957/http://washtenawtrialcourt.org/general/judge_profiles/DESresume/DESPubs/JurorsCSIMyth.pdf |archivedate=2013-06-17 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

CSI效应还有其他一些表现形式。例如公众法医学意识增强，便会要求警方在调查过程中取得更多的法医证据，导致犯罪实验室的工作量也相应膨胀。全世界范围内大学阶段法医学课程的数量和受欢迎程度都大幅增加；不过一些新的课程已经受到批评，被指其学生在面对现实法医工作时准备不足。此外，这些涉及法医科学的电视节目还有可能会让现实中的罪犯学会如何掩盖证据，因此令调查人员的破案工作变得更加困难。

